regions.title: Large diagonal wall crack above and beside the door
regions.description: This region contains a prominent, continuous diagonal crack running from above the door frame across the wall, indicating clear structural damage. The crack extends from the upper left to the lower right, passing through the areas above and beside the door.

summary: All identified cells represent one continuous region of structural damage: a major diagonal wall crack extending from above the door downward through the wall. The crack is clearly visible and the high-confidence cells accurately capture the affected area.
